The paper deals with a variant of the classic prophet inequality problem, which is a well-known problem in game theory and probability theory. The problem has connections to online sales and posted price mechanisms, which are topics in machine learning and optimization. The paper uses mathematical tools such as Schur-convexity theory, which is a topic in mathematical optimization and convex analysis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.GT (game theory), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.MA (multi-agent systems).
